			<h1>BAYADA Hospice, Boyertown, PA</h1>

			<p>Located just off Reading Avenue in the borough of Boyertown, Berks County, we provide the highest quality <a class="go" rel="leanModal" href="#Hospice">hospice</a> services to people residing in Berks, Bucks, Lehigh, and Montgomery counties. We provide clinical, social, spiritual, and emotional care so our patients can remain at home with comfort, grace, and dignity.</p>
			<p>All care is provided with compassion, excellence, and reliabilityâ€”our core values. Please visit our <a href="services-hospice.asp">services</a> page to learn more about how we can help.</p>

			<h2>Experienced hospice team</h2>
			<p>Our experienced professionals are caring members of your community who are focused entirely on hospice care. Director Angela Snyder, RN, BSN, is a lifelong resident of the community with 14 years of experience in hospice and a passion for delivering exceptional end-of-life care. Clinical Manager Cathy Barton, RN, supervises all patient care and has nearly a decade of experience in hospice care.</p>

			<h2>Our dedicated office team also includes:</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Client Services Manager</li>
					<li>Bereavement and Volunteer Coordinator</li>
					<li>Nurses</li>
					<li>Spiritual Counselors</li>
					<li>Home Health Aides</li>
					<li>Medical Social Workers</li>
				</ul><br>

			<h2>Volunteers</h2>
			<p>In addition to our office and field teams, volunteers make an important difference in the lives of our patients and their families. Some provide companionship, run errands, or help with other tasks. But no matter what they do, they are a gift! If you or someone you know would like to volunteer with us, please let us know. We provide a flexible training and orientation schedule to meet your needs.</p>
			<p>We are also a Level 3 participant in the <a href="http://wehonorveterans.org/">We Honor Veterans program</a>.</p>
                   	<h3>Contact us</h3>
                    	<p> Call us at 610-367-1608 anytime for more information or to arrange services, and our caring and knowledgeable staff will be able to help you.</p>
                  	<p>You can also stop by our office: <br>
                     	100 Schaeffer Street, Suite 4<br>
                     	Boyertown, PA 19512</p>

